Project Overview:

This project is a web application that lists events happening in Sydney, Australia. It scrapes event data from event websites and displays them in a visually appealing manner. Users can sign up to store their email addresses for future reference. The app is built with React (Vite) for the frontend and Node.js (Express) for the backend.

Features

Scrapes and displays event data dynamically.

Users can click "Get Tickets" and enter their email before being redirected.

The scraper runs every 24 hours to update event listings.

Uses MongoDB to store event data and user emails.

Tech Stack

Frontend: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS

Backend: Node.js (Express), Puppeteer (for scraping)

Database: MongoDB (Mongoose)

Styling: Tailwind CSS

Setup Instructions

Prerequisites

Node.js (v16 or later)

MongoDB installed or an Atlas cluster

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

 git clone https://github.com/your-username/event-listing-app.git
 cd event-listing-app

2️⃣ Set Up Environment Variables

Create a .env file in both frontend/ and backend/ directories with:

# Backend .env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string

# Frontend .env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

3️⃣ Install Dependencies

Run the following in both backend/ and frontend/ folders:

npm install

4️⃣ Run the Backend Server

cd backend
npm start

5️⃣ Run the Frontend

cd frontend
npm run dev

6️⃣ Access the App

Visit http://localhost:5173 in your browser.
